@endnode

@node "CanDo_anychangedbuffers" "Let {Logical}=AnyChangedBuffers"
@toc "CanDo_Buffer_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  Let {Logical}=AnyChangedBuffers

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Returns TRUE if there are any modified buffers, or else it returns FALSE.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_buffertype" "Let {BufferType}=BufferType({BufferName})"
@toc "CanDo_Buffer_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  Let {BufferType}=BufferType({BufferName})

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

Returns the Buffer type for the specified buffer.  Types are:
"Brush","BrushAnim", "Document","Icon","Picture","Read File", "Write
File","Sound".  If the buffer is not found it will return a @{" Nothing " link "CanDo_Nothing"}.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_flush" "Flush {BufferName}"
@toc "CanDo_Buffer_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  Flush {BufferName}

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Frees all memory used the buffer.  This command can fail if the buffer is
in use or has been modified in some way.
  
  SEE ALSO: @{" FlushAll " link "CanDo_FlushAll"}.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_flushall" "FlushAll"
@toc "CanDo_Buffer_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  FlushAll

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Flushes all buffers.  This command will not flush buffers that are in use
or have been modified.
  
  SEE ALSO: @{" Flush " link "CanDo_Flush"} and @{" RamScram " link "CanDo_RamScram"}.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_getbufferinfo" "GetBufferInfo {BufferName}, <Var1>, <Var2>, <Var3>, <Var4>"
@toc "CanDo_Buffer_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  GetBufferInfo {BufferName}, <Var1>, <Var2>, <Var3>, <Var4>

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Returns information about the buffer.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_insertbufferlist" "InsertBufferList"
@toc "CanDo_Buffer_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  InsertBufferList

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  This command TYPE's into the current document buffer the names of all
Buffers of the user's DECK that are currently in memory.
  
  SEE ALSO: @{" InsertChangedBufferList " link "CanDo_InsertChangedBufferList"}.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_insertchangedbufferlist" "InsertChangedBufferList"
@toc "CanDo_Buffer_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  InsertChangedBufferList

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Types the name of all modified buffers into the current document.  Each
buffer name will be on a separate line.
  
  SEE ALSO: @{" SaveAllChangedBuffers " link "CanDo_SaveAllChangedBuffers"} and @{" InsertBufferList " link "CanDo_InsertBufferList"}.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_ramscram" "RamScram"
@toc "CanDo_Buffer_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  RamScram

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Frees all Buffer Data not currently used and not modified.  CanDo does
not forget about the freed buffers and will reload them as needed.
  
  SEE ALSO: @{" Flush " link "CanDo_Flush"} and @{" FlushAll " link "CanDo_FlushAll"}.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_saveallchangedbuffers" "SaveAllChangedBuffers"
@toc "CanDo_Buffer_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  SaveAllChangedBuffers

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Saves all buffers that have been modified.  If the buffer was originally
loaded, it will save with the loaded name; otherwise, it will save with its
"Buffer Name" as its file specification.
  
  SEE ALSO: @{" InsertChangedBufferList " link "CanDo_InsertChangedBufferList"}.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_setautofilerequester" "SetAutoFileRequester {Logical}"
@toc "CanDo_Buffer_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  SetAutoFileRequester {Logical}

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Enables or disables the automatic file requester.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_setautoloadflags" "SetAutoLoadFlags <flags>"
@toc "CanDo_Buffer_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  SetAutoLoadFlags <flags>

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

Defines the buffer system's load flags.

@endnode

